### AuthLab — manual exploration via REST Client (VS Code) or JetBrains HTTP Client.
### Run AuthLab.Api first:  dotnet run --project AuthLab.Api

@base = https://localhost:7099

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Mint tokens via /dev/token
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Mint valid token
GET {{base}}/dev/token?sub=alice

### Mint admin token
GET {{base}}/dev/token?sub=alice&role=admin

### Mint expired-by-1-hour token (past default 5-min ClockSkew, will be rejected)
GET {{base}}/dev/token?sub=alice&exp=-3600

### Mint slightly expired token (within ClockSkew, will still be accepted -- JWT-V03)
GET {{base}}/dev/token?sub=alice&exp=-60

### Mint wrong-issuer token
GET {{base}}/dev/token?sub=alice&iss=https://attacker.example

### Mint wrong-audience token
GET {{base}}/dev/token?sub=alice&aud=other-api

### Mint token signed with a different key (signature should fail)
GET {{base}}/dev/token?sub=alice&key=totally-different-key-of-sufficient-length-1234567890

### Mint token with future nbf
GET {{base}}/dev/token?sub=alice&nbf=3600

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# JWT endpoint exercises -- paste a token from above into @jwt
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

@jwt = paste-token-here

### Public endpoint -- always 200
GET {{base}}/public

### /secure with no token -- expect 401 + WWW-Authenticate: Bearer
GET {{base}}/secure

### /secure with valid token
GET {{base}}/secure
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt}}

### /admin with admin role token
GET {{base}}/admin
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt}}

### JWT-V01: alg:none token (signature absent). Expect 401.
GET {{base}}/secure
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJub25lIiwidHlwIjoiSldUIn0.eyJzdWIiOiJhbGljZSIsImlzcyI6Imh0dHBzOi8vbG9jYWxob3N0OjcwOTkiLCJhdWQiOiJhdXRoLWxhYiIsImV4cCI6OTk5OTk5OTk5OSwicm9sZSI6ImFkbWluIn0.

### JWT-V04: token in query string. Expect 401 (default JwtBearer ignores it).
GET {{base}}/secure?access_token={{jwt}}

### JWT-V05: lowercase bearer prefix. Expect 200 (RFC 6750 case-insensitive).
GET {{base}}/secure
Authorization: bearer {{jwt}}

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cookie auth flow
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### C-E02: missing cookie -- expect 302 to /cookie/login
GET {{base}}/cookie/secure

### C-E01: log in (HTTP client will store the cookie)
POST {{base}}/cookie/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "user": "alice" }

### C-E01 cont'd: now access protected page
GET {{base}}/cookie/secure

### C-V01: open-redirect via ReturnUrl (intentional vuln)
POST {{base}}/cookie/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "user": "alice", "returnUrl": "https://evil.example/" }

### C-V04: CSRF-vulnerable transfer (no antiforgery)
POST {{base}}/cookie/transfer?amount=100&to=bob

### Logout
POST {{base}}/cookie/logout
